        "reference": "1Cor 14:19",
        "strongs": "G3056",
        "translit": "logos",
        "anchor_rationale": "'I would rather speak five words with my mind in order to instruct others, than ten thousand words in a tongue.' The phenomenon is explicit: words spoken with the nous (mind) reach the inner person of the hearer and instruct. Quantity is irrelevant; inner engagement of mind-to-mind is the criterion. The inner dimension of speech — the mind behind the word — determines whether it communicates."
