    {
      "code": "M15-H-VCG03",
      "label": "The word as summarising moral principle",
      "context_description": "The term names logos as the single moral principle that holds and summarises all the law's content — the whole law is fulfilled in one word: love your neighbour. The logos here is not a speech-act or a divine disclosure but an inner moral principle of such compression and completeness that it contains all specific commandments. Inner-being phenomenon: the word as comprehensive inner moral standard.",
