        "reference": "Rom 14:12",
        "strongs": "G3056",
        "translit": "logos",
        "anchor_rationale": "'Any other commandment is summed up in this word: You shall love your neighbor as yourself.' The most explicit statement of the phenomenon: logos as the single inner moral principle that holds all commandments. The compression is deliberate — the word as moral principle contains all specific moral content within itself, making it the inner standard against which all particular acts are measured."
